{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, requirements around expeditiously notifying relevant authorities if deployed generative chatbots demonstrably enable confidential data leaks (Recital 58) can enable interventions limiting damage, while avoiding knee-jerk reactions.",
    "As Recital 61 states, pragmatic coordination mechanisms recognizing anticipating challenges from technologies operating at immense scale would underscore shared responsibilities in averting crises, with the relevant notices being submitted by trusted flaggers.",
    "Following the DSA's approach of instituting oversight and communication channels by design (Article 31) (Code: DD) extends naturally to population-scale AI systems.",
    "Critiques of the DSA's approach to disinformationWhile the Digital Services Act establishes more extensive obligations on platforms compared to prior self-regulatory efforts, open questions remain regarding its efficacy and limitations.",
    "Having outlined the DSA's core provisions as well as touchpoints to AI governance, this section analyzes weaknesses in previous self-governance efforts."
  ]
}